1
00:00:32,240 --> 00:00:36,953
THE PRACTICAL GUIDE TO LOVE

2
00:00:41,749 --> 00:00:43,793
You've had too much to drink.

3
00:00:44,335 --> 00:00:46,712
Let's end the meeting here.

4
00:00:46,879 --> 00:00:48,130
I'll call you another time.

5
00:00:50,591 --> 00:00:53,386
- Where the hell are you going?
- That hurts! Let go!

6
00:00:53,469 --> 00:00:55,012
You think you can just leave?

7
00:00:55,096 --> 00:00:57,181
Let go! It hurts!

8
00:01:01,519 --> 00:01:02,687
Tae-seop!

9
00:01:02,895 --> 00:01:04,105
Who the hell are you?

10
00:01:04,188 --> 00:01:06,315
Me? Her boyfriend.

11
00:01:06,399 --> 00:01:07,400
Huh?

12
00:01:09,860 --> 00:01:11,195
- Are you okay?
- Yeah.

13
00:01:11,279 --> 00:01:12,822
Hold up. What did you just say?

14
00:01:13,406 --> 00:01:14,991
You had a boyfriend all along?

15
00:01:16,284 --> 00:01:17,743
Damn it!

16
00:01:18,119 --> 00:01:20,454
Why would he set me up with a woman
who's already taken?

17
00:01:21,330 --> 00:01:22,915
Set you up?

18
00:01:24,083 --> 00:01:25,751
Who set you up with me?

19
00:01:28,462 --> 00:01:29,714
I knew something was off.

20
00:01:29,797 --> 00:01:32,842
I'm not going to let this slide.

21
00:01:32,925 --> 00:01:35,344
Don't even dream
of getting your hands on our products!

22
00:01:35,428 --> 00:01:37,263
Please stop there and leave.

23
00:01:37,763 --> 00:01:40,099
Why do you keep interrupting us?

24
00:01:40,182 --> 00:01:42,518
Better me interrupting than the police.

25
00:01:42,810 --> 00:01:45,646
You've got a lot of eyes watching.
And the CCTV is filming it all.

26
00:01:57,658 --> 00:01:58,868
Damn it!

27
00:02:05,499 --> 00:02:07,084
Good luck getting your damn cattle!

28
00:02:08,169 --> 00:02:10,421
- Are you okay?
- Yeah.

29
00:02:10,588 --> 00:02:11,922
Does your wrist hurt a lot? Let me see.

30
00:02:13,341 --> 00:02:14,634
Oh, gosh.

31
00:02:15,426 --> 00:02:16,469
That jerk.

32
00:02:18,971 --> 00:02:20,765
By the way

33
00:02:20,848 --> 00:02:22,850
how did you know to come here?

34
00:02:22,933 --> 00:02:24,060
Oh, well...

35
00:02:25,061 --> 00:02:27,188
Mr. Shin called me.

36
00:02:27,772 --> 00:02:29,690
- Ji-su?
- Yeah.

37
00:02:34,945 --> 00:02:37,615
I keep thinking about someone else.

38
00:02:37,698 --> 00:02:39,950
I promise not to cross the line.

39
00:02:40,242 --> 00:02:42,328
I won't bother you. All good now?

40
00:03:12,775 --> 00:03:14,735
How could I not have realized this?

41
00:03:14,819 --> 00:03:17,113
Don't beat yourself up over it.
You should be mad.

42
00:03:19,699 --> 00:03:21,575
Let's go. I'll drive you home.

43
00:03:38,467 --> 00:03:43,139
THE PRACTICAL GUIDE TO LOVE
EPISODE 10

44
00:03:43,973 --> 00:03:47,226
Mr. Oh seems to have set you up
for that meeting because it was a date.

45
00:03:47,393 --> 00:03:50,396
From what you've told me,
it seems like the guy knew it was a date.

46
00:03:51,814 --> 00:03:54,483
- Touch it.
- What? No, thanks.

47
00:03:54,567 --> 00:03:55,985
You're old enough to know everything.

48
00:03:56,068 --> 00:03:59,947
It's not fun
when a woman keeps acting so innocent.

49
00:04:00,030 --> 00:04:01,866
So, how many men have you dated?

50
00:04:01,949 --> 00:04:03,451
Three? Four?

51
00:04:05,077 --> 00:04:07,163
But why would Mr. Oh do that?

52
00:04:07,246 --> 00:04:08,831
He must've wanted to make this happen

53
00:04:08,914 --> 00:04:10,875
knowing how keen
the Senior Managing Director was.

54
00:04:10,958 --> 00:04:13,627
He probably didn't think
anything would go wrong over one dinner.

55
00:04:13,753 --> 00:04:16,589
I know you've gone
on a lot of blind dates lately.

56
00:04:16,672 --> 00:04:17,923
But as you know

57
00:04:18,007 --> 00:04:20,843
blind dates are good experience,
even if things don't work out.

58
00:04:20,968 --> 00:04:23,179
And sometimes, you get lucky
and find a good one.

59
00:04:23,304 --> 00:04:24,305
Take the card.

60
00:04:24,805 --> 00:04:28,100
Order whatever you want with it, okay?

61
00:04:31,812 --> 00:04:35,858
How could he do this?
It was a work meeting.

62
00:04:35,941 --> 00:04:38,861
I can't let this slide, either.

63
00:04:38,944 --> 00:04:40,946
He totally undermined us.

64
00:04:41,113 --> 00:04:43,532
I'll file a formal complaint
with the hotel.

65
00:04:57,087 --> 00:04:58,714
LIVESTOCK ENVIRONMENT MANAGEMENT AGENCY

66
00:05:00,049 --> 00:05:01,050
WHAT'S GOING ON IN THE CONFERENCE ROOM?

67
00:05:02,551 --> 00:05:03,636
IS SOMETHING WRONG AT PURCHASING?

68
00:05:03,719 --> 00:05:04,845
I HEAR MR. OH HAD A BIG FIGHT
WITH HIS TEAMMATES

69
00:05:05,638 --> 00:05:07,515
Why are they getting so nosy
about nothing?

70
00:05:08,724 --> 00:05:10,976
As if it's not bad enough already.

71
00:05:35,417 --> 00:05:36,502
How did it go?

72
00:05:37,127 --> 00:05:39,630
I just recounted everything that happened

73
00:05:39,797 --> 00:05:42,132
from the sudden change
in the project manager

74
00:05:42,258 --> 00:05:44,260
to the things that happened to Ui-yeong.

75
00:05:44,885 --> 00:05:48,514
Mr. Oh is having a meeting
with the Grievance Committee.

76
00:05:49,473 --> 00:05:51,475
OFFICE AUTOMATION ROOM

77
00:05:51,559 --> 00:05:53,269
Let's get some coffee.

78
00:06:24,091 --> 00:06:26,218
- Ui-yeong.
- Mr. Oh.

79
00:06:28,721 --> 00:06:29,763
Well...

80
00:06:30,931 --> 00:06:31,932
I'm sorry.

81
00:06:32,850 --> 00:06:35,227
I thought it'd make things easier

82
00:06:36,020 --> 00:06:39,773
if the people working on the project
got along...

83
00:06:41,942 --> 00:06:44,278
No, I have no excuse.

84
00:06:46,030 --> 00:06:47,781
I'm really sorry this time.

85
00:06:49,450 --> 00:06:50,910
This won't ever happen again.

86
00:06:52,620 --> 00:06:53,787
I promise you that.

87
00:06:54,830 --> 00:06:56,248
Okay.

88
00:06:57,291 --> 00:06:58,375
Sorry.

89
00:07:23,859 --> 00:07:26,236
Ui-yeong,
you haven't had lunch yet, right?

90
00:07:36,372 --> 00:07:38,040
We'll take two of the chef's specials.

91
00:07:38,123 --> 00:07:40,417
- Okay, I'll get that ready right away.
- Thank you.

92
00:07:42,127 --> 00:07:43,128
Well...

93
00:07:43,587 --> 00:07:46,215
I should've at least changed
out of my uniform.

94
00:07:47,174 --> 00:07:48,968
It's fine.

95
00:07:49,051 --> 00:07:51,220
We're here as guests.

96
00:07:51,637 --> 00:07:54,556
And the hotel doesn't own this place.
It's an outside vendor.

97
00:07:54,640 --> 00:07:56,225
We don't even get employee discounts.

98
00:07:56,308 --> 00:07:59,728
Don't be shy and enjoy it all.

99
00:08:07,361 --> 00:08:09,196
This is such a fancy lunch.

100
00:08:09,279 --> 00:08:12,574
You need to enjoy something good
to make yourself feel better.

101
00:08:12,741 --> 00:08:13,784
Dig in.

102
00:08:15,077 --> 00:08:17,204
Sorry for not appreciating you
as our key employee

103
00:08:17,287 --> 00:08:21,667
when we were prioritizing the hotel
over you.

104
00:08:21,750 --> 00:08:22,835
It's okay.

105
00:08:25,004 --> 00:08:26,630
Mr. Oh apologized

106
00:08:27,214 --> 00:08:29,133
and you've gone so far
to make me feel better.

107
00:08:29,508 --> 00:08:32,386
I don't think I'll remember this
as being that bad.

108
00:08:36,724 --> 00:08:40,436
You've been working at our hotel
for about ten years now, right?

109
00:08:42,104 --> 00:08:43,105
Yeah.

110
00:08:44,023 --> 00:08:49,069
You'll get burnt out at the hotel
if you let something like this slide.

111
00:08:49,528 --> 00:08:53,198
So, until the Disciplinary Committee
decides what to do with Mr. Oh

112
00:08:54,033 --> 00:08:57,494
we want to give you a few days off.

113
00:08:58,245 --> 00:08:59,455
A few days off?

114
00:09:00,581 --> 00:09:05,127
But I have a lot on my plate right now.
I need to look for another producer, too.

115
00:09:05,794 --> 00:09:08,297
Oh, I thought you'd be excited.

116
00:09:09,506 --> 00:09:12,134
Come to think of it,
you haven't had a proper vacation yet.

117
00:09:12,217 --> 00:09:14,803
You also went straight through college
without a break.

118
00:09:15,763 --> 00:09:17,765
- Yeah.
- As admirable as that is

119
00:09:18,640 --> 00:09:20,559
sometimes, I feel bad for you.

120
00:09:22,352 --> 00:09:25,314
Na-ri's determined to do well now,
so don't worry.

121
00:09:25,731 --> 00:09:27,900
Why don't you take this chance

122
00:09:27,983 --> 00:09:31,737
to take some time for yourself?

123
00:09:36,492 --> 00:09:38,577
Okay, I will.

124
00:09:39,161 --> 00:09:41,580
Okay, keep eating. It's good soup.

125
00:09:41,663 --> 00:09:43,373
Okay, thank you.

126
00:09:53,759 --> 00:09:56,845
- Hey, Mom.
- What are you doing? Don't you have work?

127
00:09:57,179 --> 00:09:58,931
Oh, I got a few days off.

128
00:09:59,389 --> 00:10:01,433
But my body still thinks
it's time for work.

129
00:10:01,767 --> 00:10:02,851
That's random.

130
00:10:03,685 --> 00:10:04,853
Did you do something wrong?

131
00:10:04,937 --> 00:10:06,396
No, I was wronged...

132
00:10:06,605 --> 00:10:09,399
No, they just told me
to get some rest and recharge.

133
00:10:10,317 --> 00:10:12,736
Didn't I tell you to stand your ground

134
00:10:12,820 --> 00:10:15,781
to keep people from undermining you?

135
00:10:16,240 --> 00:10:18,033
Nobody undermines me as much as you do.

136
00:10:18,117 --> 00:10:20,661
Stop nagging. Just get to work.

137
00:10:21,745 --> 00:10:22,996
Clean the house.

138
00:10:23,455 --> 00:10:25,582
- You don't get a day off from chores.
- My gosh.

139
00:10:26,083 --> 00:10:27,334
What's your plan now?

140
00:10:27,417 --> 00:10:29,128
Don't worry. I have plenty to do!

141
00:10:29,211 --> 00:10:31,004
- Just go!
- Okay, bye.

142
00:10:31,088 --> 00:10:32,798
- Have a good day.
- Bye.

143
00:10:34,591 --> 00:10:35,592
What should I do now?

144
00:10:40,556 --> 00:10:44,059
There's nothing to do.
Can't believe I came to the gym myself.

145
00:10:45,435 --> 00:10:47,896
I just started,
and I'm already getting flooded with work.

146
00:10:48,522 --> 00:10:51,108
Oh, no.
Maybe this will make you feel better.

147
00:10:51,191 --> 00:10:53,026
OH, NO.
MAYBE THIS WILL MAKE YOU FEEL BETTER

148
00:10:56,363 --> 00:10:58,323
I'll need to see your forearms
to feel better.

149
00:11:03,412 --> 00:11:05,539
Take a photo of your face or your arms,
not both.

150
00:11:05,789 --> 00:11:08,208
You think you can make both look good
in one photo?

151
00:11:14,381 --> 00:11:19,178
I'LL NEED TO SEE YOUR FOREARMS
TO FEEL BETTER

152
00:11:19,803 --> 00:11:21,054
I definitely feel better now!

153
00:11:29,646 --> 00:11:32,316
Hyun-min, any updates on the market visit?

154
00:11:32,441 --> 00:11:33,609
No, nothing.

155
00:11:33,692 --> 00:11:36,361
But the reporter who wrote
about tiger cattle replied

156
00:11:36,445 --> 00:11:38,780
so I'll ask her
about the farm in the article.

157
00:11:38,864 --> 00:11:39,865
From a reporter?

158
00:11:40,240 --> 00:11:42,492
Hold on. Why is everyone reading the chat?

159
00:11:43,243 --> 00:11:45,120
Ui-yeong, you're reading the chat!

160
00:11:45,579 --> 00:11:47,539
Let's leave this chat and start a new one.

161
00:11:47,664 --> 00:11:49,291
No, wait!

162
00:11:49,666 --> 00:11:51,168
Come on.

163
00:11:51,293 --> 00:11:54,254
You can work or rest, but not both.

164
00:11:54,880 --> 00:11:57,299
I'll have to take care of all of it
once I'm back, anyway.

165
00:11:58,175 --> 00:12:02,137
Come on. You know things you've been
putting off because you've been busy.

166
00:12:02,721 --> 00:12:04,223
Do those, one by one.

167
00:12:07,851 --> 00:12:10,646
Hey, how come you're not making me
do squats or lunges

168
00:12:10,729 --> 00:12:13,023
when you're not the one on vacation
right now?

169
00:12:13,148 --> 00:12:15,400
Alright, get into the plank pose
right now.

170
00:12:16,485 --> 00:12:18,737
You're lying facing up?
Let's do leg raises.

171
00:12:18,946 --> 00:12:21,531
To the side? Let's work your obliques.

172
00:12:21,615 --> 00:12:23,575
Tighten your core muscles!

173
00:12:23,659 --> 00:12:25,786
WISHLIST: A RELAXED MORNING, READING,
SPENDING TIME WITH MOM, TRYING A NEW THING

174
00:12:25,869 --> 00:12:28,872
I've been putting off tons of things
because I haven't had time.

175
00:12:37,673 --> 00:12:38,674
Oh!

176
00:12:40,926 --> 00:12:42,177
A DATE WITH TAE-SEOP

177
00:12:42,302 --> 00:12:43,303
A date.

178
00:12:47,432 --> 00:12:48,433
What else?

179
00:12:48,517 --> 00:12:50,686
- See you.
- No, wait!

180
00:12:51,520 --> 00:12:52,938
Ta-da! It's for you.

181
00:12:53,605 --> 00:12:54,690
What?

182
00:12:55,524 --> 00:12:56,733
- Thanks.
- You're welcome.

183
00:12:56,817 --> 00:12:58,527
- Have a good day!
- Bye!

184
00:13:09,913 --> 00:13:11,081
It smells so nice.

185
00:13:20,549 --> 00:13:24,303
ENJOYING A RELAXING MORNING, CHECK

186
00:13:28,849 --> 00:13:32,477
READING A BOOK, CHECK

187
00:13:40,861 --> 00:13:42,779
I don't like things that hurt.

188
00:13:43,071 --> 00:13:46,033
My colleague is scared of everything

189
00:13:46,283 --> 00:13:47,659
and she said this was painless.

190
00:13:47,909 --> 00:13:49,703
It's about time you got some work done.

191
00:13:50,537 --> 00:13:52,914
If it's so good, why don't you get it?

192
00:13:52,998 --> 00:13:55,500
Let me be a good daughter for once,
alright?

193
00:14:03,383 --> 00:14:05,635
You can sleep if you get sleepy.

194
00:14:05,927 --> 00:14:07,012
Okay.

195
00:14:09,431 --> 00:14:11,266
How is it? Do you like it?

196
00:14:15,771 --> 00:14:20,025
DOING A FULL-BODY STRETCH, CHECK

197
00:14:20,108 --> 00:14:22,736
- Slowly!
- Here we go!

198
00:14:24,905 --> 00:14:25,989
Stop it!

199
00:14:26,073 --> 00:14:27,783
You're so stiff.

200
00:14:28,617 --> 00:14:29,618
That hurts.

201
00:14:30,077 --> 00:14:31,244
Go like this.

202
00:14:35,749 --> 00:14:37,376
PARK JEONG-IM

203
00:14:38,752 --> 00:14:39,878
Hello.

204
00:14:40,962 --> 00:14:42,089
- Jeong-im.
- Yeah?

205
00:14:42,172 --> 00:14:44,216
Why don't you eat lunch with us
these days?

206
00:14:44,424 --> 00:14:47,219
My daughter's on vacation

207
00:14:47,302 --> 00:14:49,304
and I guess
she likes making breakfast now.

208
00:14:50,180 --> 00:14:51,973
She made me lunch, so I had this instead.

209
00:14:52,307 --> 00:14:54,184
She makes lunches for you
while on vacation?

210
00:14:54,393 --> 00:14:56,144
What a kind daughter you have!

211
00:14:56,228 --> 00:14:59,022
You wouldn't be saying that
if you'd actually tasted it.

212
00:15:00,190 --> 00:15:01,691
Did you schedule your physical?

213
00:15:01,858 --> 00:15:03,110
Oh, right.

214
00:15:04,194 --> 00:15:05,987
You want to go with me this year, too?

215
00:15:07,531 --> 00:15:09,366
I don't mean to show off

216
00:15:09,616 --> 00:15:12,327
but my son asked me first,
so I've already booked an appointment.

217
00:15:12,411 --> 00:15:14,079
We're going to an all-you-can-eat, too!

218
00:15:14,162 --> 00:15:16,289
- That'll be a nice date.
- Yeah.

219
00:15:16,373 --> 00:15:18,834
You should go with your daughter, too.

220
00:15:18,917 --> 00:15:20,585
She'll keep you company.

221
00:15:20,669 --> 00:15:23,839
Me? No, I'll just go by myself.

222
00:15:24,005 --> 00:15:28,218
I don't know what she's doing,
but she seems so busy.

223
00:15:32,722 --> 00:15:34,099
Am I painting this?

224
00:15:34,182 --> 00:15:35,851
- Yeah.
- What if I ruin it?

225
00:15:36,685 --> 00:15:38,145
It's okay, I'll show you.

226
00:15:39,521 --> 00:15:41,022
Watch what I do.

227
00:15:42,983 --> 00:15:46,027
Just spread it evenly, like this.

228
00:15:46,736 --> 00:15:48,238
- Here.
- That sounds fun.

229
00:15:48,905 --> 00:15:51,616
Hold on. You should tie your hair.

230
00:15:53,285 --> 00:15:55,078
Let me do it for you.

231
00:15:57,289 --> 00:15:58,623
You know how to tie hair?

232
00:15:58,707 --> 00:15:59,708
No.

233
00:16:01,084 --> 00:16:02,085
Like this.

234
00:16:03,378 --> 00:16:04,379
Go!

235
00:16:05,297 --> 00:16:06,339
All good now.

236
00:16:08,175 --> 00:16:09,551
- Here I go.
- Okay.

237
00:16:10,010 --> 00:16:11,178
Get some of this...

238
00:16:17,559 --> 00:16:19,019
Yes, just spread that.

239
00:16:20,937 --> 00:16:21,938
You're doing great.

240
00:16:22,772 --> 00:16:24,274
I think I'm better than you.

241
00:16:24,357 --> 00:16:25,442
TRYING SOMETHING NEW, CHECK
A DATE WITH TAE-SEOP, CHECK

242
00:16:25,525 --> 00:16:27,360
- You're talented.
- This is fun.

243
00:16:28,195 --> 00:16:30,489
You're really getting the hang
of this vacation thing.

244
00:16:30,655 --> 00:16:32,324
You're not talking about work at all.

245
00:16:32,532 --> 00:16:34,910
I have no time to think about work
when I'm so busy.

246
00:16:34,993 --> 00:16:38,330
Woodworking is like meditation.

247
00:16:38,622 --> 00:16:40,790
You stop overthinking
when you get in the zone.

248
00:16:41,374 --> 00:16:43,043
- I get it.
- Right?

249
00:16:43,960 --> 00:16:45,170
You're so good.

250
00:16:45,253 --> 00:16:47,422
- I think I'm actually talented.
- Yeah.

251
00:16:50,133 --> 00:16:53,261
You just need to keep it somewhere cool
to dry for 24 hours.

252
00:16:53,345 --> 00:16:54,387
I see.

253
00:17:01,144 --> 00:17:02,562
I have something to show you.

254
00:17:03,271 --> 00:17:04,898
- What?
- Ta-da!

255
00:17:06,149 --> 00:17:07,234
It's a photo!

256
00:17:09,653 --> 00:17:14,449
I'll trade this for the baby photo of you
I said I wanted.

257
00:17:14,699 --> 00:17:15,700
Okay.

258
00:17:16,493 --> 00:17:19,162
You were beautiful, even as a kid.

259
00:17:19,996 --> 00:17:21,957
Were you on a trip to the beach?

260
00:17:22,290 --> 00:17:25,377
Yeah, I was about seven or eight.

261
00:17:25,460 --> 00:17:28,421
This was from a summer trip
with my parents.

262
00:17:29,464 --> 00:17:33,051
This was probably the last family trip
we took together.

263
00:17:35,428 --> 00:17:37,305
I remember it feeling...

264
00:17:37,389 --> 00:17:41,518
so warm and wonderful.

265
00:17:42,102 --> 00:17:45,605
But I don't remember anything
aside from feeling that way in the moment.

266
00:17:46,231 --> 00:17:49,317
Because you don't realize
it's a special moment when you're a kid.

267
00:17:49,401 --> 00:17:50,485
I know.

268
00:17:50,569 --> 00:17:54,239
I would've cherished such a moment
if I were to have it now.

269
00:17:55,031 --> 00:17:57,284
I wouldn't even forget it,
even if someone told me to.

270
00:17:59,452 --> 00:18:00,495
Like right now.

271
00:18:01,663 --> 00:18:03,540
- Right now?
- Yeah.

272
00:18:04,666 --> 00:18:06,418
When would I ever get a spontaneous break

273
00:18:06,543 --> 00:18:08,712
and spend time with you like this

274
00:18:08,795 --> 00:18:12,966
under the excuse of trying something new?

275
00:18:13,049 --> 00:18:16,303
You're right. This is really precious.

276
00:18:16,386 --> 00:18:17,804
I know.

277
00:18:22,976 --> 00:18:24,102
Don't I look better now?

278
00:18:25,270 --> 00:18:27,522
- I don't think so.
- So mean!

279
00:18:47,167 --> 00:18:48,960
Oh, gosh! What?

280
00:18:49,294 --> 00:18:51,671
I e-mailed and texted you
yesterday and today

281
00:18:51,755 --> 00:18:53,423
but you didn't reply, so here I am.

282
00:18:54,591 --> 00:18:55,675
Check it out.

283
00:18:57,719 --> 00:18:59,387
Sorry!

284
00:18:59,929 --> 00:19:04,100
I've just been all over the place.

285
00:19:04,768 --> 00:19:07,062
But the contract's about to be signed

286
00:19:07,145 --> 00:19:10,231
and the gift set is coming along nicely.

287
00:19:11,858 --> 00:19:14,152
Hold on tight. It's the weekend soon.

288
00:19:15,153 --> 00:19:16,154
Thanks.

289
00:19:16,571 --> 00:19:19,282
Yeah, it's almost the weekend.

290
00:19:19,366 --> 00:19:21,284
Hello, Chef.

291
00:19:25,163 --> 00:19:26,247
Hyun-min.

292
00:19:27,040 --> 00:19:28,041
What?

293
00:19:28,249 --> 00:19:31,503
You'll need to visit the cattle farm
this weekend.

294
00:19:32,045 --> 00:19:33,046
What?

295
00:19:34,297 --> 00:19:36,549
Sorry, there's just not enough time.

296
00:19:36,716 --> 00:19:39,761
Just do a site visit
and get the contract signed.

297
00:19:40,011 --> 00:19:41,346
Na-ri!

298
00:19:42,055 --> 00:19:44,766
How can you steal my weekend from me?

299
00:19:46,685 --> 00:19:48,269
It's not like I get to rest, either!

300
00:19:48,395 --> 00:19:50,730
I'll take care of everything else

301
00:19:50,980 --> 00:19:52,565
so just take care of the farm for me.

302
00:19:53,274 --> 00:19:54,401
Alright...

303
00:19:57,904 --> 00:19:59,114
Ui-yeong!

304
00:20:00,240 --> 00:20:01,616
I miss you.

305
00:20:04,744 --> 00:20:06,037
- Ui-yeong!
- Oh!

306
00:20:06,955 --> 00:20:09,791
Ui-yeong!

307
00:20:09,874 --> 00:20:10,917
How have you been?

308
00:20:11,751 --> 00:20:14,254
How are you? I missed you!

309
00:20:14,379 --> 00:20:15,797
It's only been a few days.

310
00:20:16,047 --> 00:20:18,258
It's like I lost my youth
the moment you left.

311
00:20:18,383 --> 00:20:20,468
I realized how precious you were
once you left.

312
00:20:21,511 --> 00:20:25,140
Let's go.
I chose the best restaurant for you!

313
00:20:25,223 --> 00:20:26,891
I can't wait! Let's head in.

314
00:20:28,852 --> 00:20:30,603
Let's go.

315
00:20:31,479 --> 00:20:33,356
The portion size is huge!

316
00:20:33,648 --> 00:20:35,817
- Thanks.
- Enjoy!

317
00:20:44,451 --> 00:20:46,077
- It's so good.
- Right?

318
00:20:46,161 --> 00:20:47,495
I told you it was good.

319
00:20:50,999 --> 00:20:54,669
Did you really want to see me
just to grab dinner together?

320
00:20:55,879 --> 00:20:58,590
The office feels so empty without you.

321
00:20:59,382 --> 00:21:03,428
All I do is work when I'm not sleeping.

322
00:21:03,511 --> 00:21:05,889
I don't even have time to see
my new boyfriend.

323
00:21:06,806 --> 00:21:09,267
Na-ri told me to visit the cattle farm
for a site visit

324
00:21:09,350 --> 00:21:11,227
and to sign the contract over the weekend.

325
00:21:12,103 --> 00:21:14,272
But I've never signed a contract alone

326
00:21:14,355 --> 00:21:16,065
so I wanted to ask you a few questions.

327
00:21:16,357 --> 00:21:17,442
Where's the farm?

328
00:21:17,525 --> 00:21:19,402
Sokcho, Gangwon-do.

329
00:21:19,819 --> 00:21:20,904
Sokcho...

330
00:21:22,363 --> 00:21:23,573
You want me to go with you?

331
00:21:25,241 --> 00:21:26,326
Really?

332
00:21:26,409 --> 00:21:28,286
You're treating me to a good dinner

333
00:21:28,453 --> 00:21:30,538
and I might as well make a trip out of it.

334
00:21:31,289 --> 00:21:34,083
I'd love to have you join me!

335
00:21:34,209 --> 00:21:37,712
I'll book our hotel and buses.

336
00:21:37,879 --> 00:21:38,880
Just bring yourself.

337
00:21:38,963 --> 00:21:41,549
And I won't bother you in our free time.

338
00:21:41,633 --> 00:21:43,092
Okay, let's go together.

339
00:21:43,551 --> 00:21:45,345
You're an angel!

340
00:21:46,179 --> 00:21:47,597
- Eat up!
- Okay.

341
00:21:48,848 --> 00:21:50,475
I'm home.

342
00:21:51,142 --> 00:21:52,393
Where were you?

343
00:21:52,477 --> 00:21:54,229
I had dinner with a coworker.

344
00:21:54,479 --> 00:21:55,522
I see.

345
00:21:56,231 --> 00:21:58,358
Are you getting a physical?

346
00:21:58,900 --> 00:22:00,109
Yeah.

347
00:22:01,444 --> 00:22:05,031
You want to watch a movie
if you're free this weekend?

348
00:22:05,365 --> 00:22:06,866
No, I can't.

349
00:22:06,991 --> 00:22:09,410
I need to go to Sokcho to sign a contract.

350
00:22:09,619 --> 00:22:11,955
My colleague's too scared to do it alone.

351
00:22:13,206 --> 00:22:14,749
On your last weekend off?

352
00:22:16,000 --> 00:22:18,253
That should get you ready for Monday,
at least.

353
00:22:18,670 --> 00:22:19,838
I guess so.

354
00:22:20,797 --> 00:22:23,258
I can't believe my vacation's ending.

355
00:22:29,180 --> 00:22:35,478
HKUH CENTER FOR CANCER RESEARCH
DONATION AWARDING CEREMONY

356
00:22:36,354 --> 00:22:39,274
You'll hand out the certificates
to the big donors

357
00:22:39,357 --> 00:22:42,652
and take photos with them,
which will be published in an article.

358
00:22:42,735 --> 00:22:45,822
I think
you left my wife off the guest list.

359
00:22:45,905 --> 00:22:48,241
Did she not tell you?

360
00:22:48,324 --> 00:22:51,077
She called and said
she'd donate the amount she promised

361
00:22:51,160 --> 00:22:53,371
but would not be attending the event.

362
00:22:55,123 --> 00:22:56,165
I see.

363
00:22:59,335 --> 00:23:01,170
- Okay, then.
- Okay.

364
00:23:01,254 --> 00:23:06,384
HKUH CENTER FOR CANCER RESEARCH
DONATION AWARDING CEREMONY

365
00:23:12,098 --> 00:23:13,933
The caller is unavailable.

366
00:23:14,100 --> 00:23:17,353
Please record your message after the beep.

367
00:23:21,316 --> 00:23:25,194
CALL HISTORY

368
00:23:28,907 --> 00:23:32,410
At least I know she's being selective
about who to answer.

369
00:23:34,913 --> 00:23:35,955
Come in.

370
00:23:41,920 --> 00:23:43,004
You can leave it.

371
00:23:56,059 --> 00:23:57,185
SEOUL FAMILY COURT

372
00:24:09,030 --> 00:24:12,742
SEOUL FAMILY COURT

373
00:24:15,036 --> 00:24:17,580
COMPLAINT FILED BY SON JEONG-A
AGAINST SHIN JI-HUN

374
00:24:23,461 --> 00:24:25,129
- Thank you.
- Come again.

375
00:24:27,757 --> 00:24:28,800
Sorry.

376
00:24:31,302 --> 00:24:32,345
Hello.

377
00:24:34,013 --> 00:24:35,473
- Ji-su!
- Yeah?

378
00:24:40,478 --> 00:24:43,272
I've been a fan of yours forever.

379
00:24:43,564 --> 00:24:46,693
- Could I have your autograph?
- Of course. What's your name?

380
00:24:47,151 --> 00:24:49,278
It's Song Cheol.

381
00:24:50,363 --> 00:24:54,492
Please write "For Cheol"
and today's date, too.

382
00:24:55,994 --> 00:24:57,078
Thank you!

383
00:24:57,578 --> 00:24:59,956
You can drink and eat whatever you want.

384
00:25:00,164 --> 00:25:02,500
Ji-su, don't let her pay, okay?

385
00:25:09,340 --> 00:25:11,801
I'll take one hand-drip coffee. Hot.

386
00:25:19,392 --> 00:25:21,477
Don't you have other cafes in Seoul
you can go to?

387
00:25:22,645 --> 00:25:24,814
What happened to doing your best
to avoid me?

388
00:25:25,815 --> 00:25:27,150
I came to tell you something.

389
00:25:27,859 --> 00:25:29,444
It wasn't anything to text you about.

390
00:25:31,904 --> 00:25:33,322
I'm not interested.

391
00:25:34,699 --> 00:25:35,783
You're so cold.

392
00:25:35,992 --> 00:25:38,870
I'm getting a divorce.

393
00:25:39,412 --> 00:25:40,413
What?

394
00:25:49,464 --> 00:25:50,590
Are you serious?

395
00:25:51,674 --> 00:25:54,135
You seem quite shaken
for someone who isn't interested.

396
00:25:55,344 --> 00:25:56,846
We're processing it quietly.

397
00:25:57,930 --> 00:25:59,807
You acted like Romeo and Juliet.

398
00:26:01,768 --> 00:26:03,311
And it's over, just like that?

399
00:26:04,187 --> 00:26:06,856
I didn't expect a disappointing ending
when I fell in love.

400
00:26:07,648 --> 00:26:08,941
But I recently found out

401
00:26:10,401 --> 00:26:12,570
that he lied to get with me.

402
00:26:14,072 --> 00:26:16,407
I checked your mother's medical record
with my own eyes.

403
00:26:18,618 --> 00:26:21,412
He was seeing me
while she was undergoing chemo.

404
00:26:24,707 --> 00:26:25,875
I had no idea.

405
00:26:27,710 --> 00:26:28,711
No

406
00:26:29,629 --> 00:26:31,255
maybe I just let myself be blinded.

407
00:26:32,048 --> 00:26:33,841
When you're deeply in love

408
00:26:33,925 --> 00:26:37,720
you want to reject the truth,
no matter how desperately it knocks.

409
00:26:37,929 --> 00:26:41,349
Love that makes you numb
to someone else's pain.

410
00:26:41,557 --> 00:26:42,767
Isn't it disgusting?

411
00:26:44,477 --> 00:26:45,478
But...

412
00:26:47,021 --> 00:26:49,065
the truth feels so important now.

413
00:26:52,193 --> 00:26:53,277
I'm sorry.

414
00:26:53,778 --> 00:26:54,821
After all that?

415
00:26:55,947 --> 00:26:57,281
I'm sorry it took me so long.

416
00:26:58,574 --> 00:26:59,867
I'm really sorry.

417
00:27:01,119 --> 00:27:02,245
I mean it.

418
00:27:21,681 --> 00:27:23,683
- Hello, Director.
- Hello.

419
00:27:24,934 --> 00:27:25,935
- Hello.
- Hello.

420
00:27:26,018 --> 00:27:28,437
- Hello.
- Hello.

421
00:27:30,815 --> 00:27:31,941
Hello, Director.

422
00:27:36,070 --> 00:27:37,113
- Hey.
- Yeah?

423
00:27:37,196 --> 00:27:38,698
You really sure about his outfit?

424
00:27:39,448 --> 00:27:41,284
He looks like a model,
not a new detective.

425
00:27:42,076 --> 00:27:45,288
I'll ask the stylist to make
his hair and outfit look more natural.

426
00:27:47,206 --> 00:27:48,958
Go to the dressing room in ten.

427
00:27:49,208 --> 00:27:50,209
Okay.

428
00:27:53,880 --> 00:27:57,133
So, you're the one who got hired
because of Jeong-a.

429
00:27:57,925 --> 00:27:58,968
Sorry?

430
00:27:59,135 --> 00:28:02,763
I hear she's considering another project
over this director's.

431
00:28:04,056 --> 00:28:06,434
Oh, she got you a role
before she ditched him!

432
00:28:06,517 --> 00:28:08,269
No wonder the director's bitter.

433
00:28:10,897 --> 00:28:12,064
But he's handsome.

434
00:28:13,566 --> 00:28:16,444
Are you leaving on Saturday
and returning on Sunday?

435
00:28:17,028 --> 00:28:20,323
Yeah, I'll just visit the farm
and travel around the area.

436
00:28:20,531 --> 00:28:24,785
Oh, the beach in the photo I gave you is
in Sokcho.

437
00:28:24,869 --> 00:28:26,537
I want to go since it's been so long.

438
00:28:26,662 --> 00:28:27,747
I see.

439
00:28:28,539 --> 00:28:30,249
Why don't I tag along?

440
00:28:31,167 --> 00:28:32,210
You?

441
00:28:32,293 --> 00:28:34,378
You have to get back to work soon

442
00:28:34,462 --> 00:28:36,714
so it'll be nice to go on a trip,
even if it's short.

443
00:28:36,964 --> 00:28:39,634
Or would I be a nuisance?

444
00:28:41,385 --> 00:28:42,386
SONG TAE-SEOP

445
00:28:43,554 --> 00:28:45,473
Oh, no.

446
00:28:45,681 --> 00:28:47,433
We're hanging out after work, anyway.

447
00:28:47,516 --> 00:28:49,018
I'll go when you're done.

448
00:28:49,477 --> 00:28:51,646
Let's go to the beach, eat some good food

449
00:28:51,729 --> 00:28:53,189
and I'll drive you back on Sunday.

450
00:28:53,272 --> 00:28:54,273
Sounds good.

451
00:28:55,066 --> 00:28:56,067
This is exciting.

452
00:28:57,276 --> 00:28:58,736
- Okay.
- Bye.

453
00:29:04,283 --> 00:29:06,118
Our first overnight trip?

454
00:29:10,790 --> 00:29:12,416
Mom! I'm heading out.

455
00:29:12,500 --> 00:29:13,793
Oh, okay.

456
00:29:13,918 --> 00:29:15,503
It's an overnight trip, right?

457
00:29:15,753 --> 00:29:18,422
Yeah, don't skip your meals.

458
00:29:18,714 --> 00:29:20,675
And it's okay to see a movie alone, too.

459
00:29:20,967 --> 00:29:22,927
Alright, get going.

460
00:29:23,010 --> 00:29:25,096
- Okay, bye!
- Bye.

461
00:29:30,101 --> 00:29:32,061
Ui-yeong!

462
00:29:32,144 --> 00:29:33,145
Hey.

463
00:29:36,023 --> 00:29:37,817
Thanks so much for tagging along.

464
00:29:37,900 --> 00:29:41,654
It's nothing.
It'll be nice to go to the beach and all.

465
00:29:42,321 --> 00:29:44,657
Alright, it's a trip, then! Let's go!

466
00:29:44,740 --> 00:29:45,741
Let's go!

467
00:29:51,038 --> 00:29:54,333
- They're tiger cattle from Gangwon-do.
- I see.

468
00:29:54,417 --> 00:29:56,252
The meat is very firm and juicy.

469
00:29:56,335 --> 00:29:59,672
Look at them.
They're different from regular cows.

470
00:29:59,839 --> 00:30:01,340
You see the dark ones?

471
00:30:01,424 --> 00:30:03,342
They're different from the other cows.

472
00:30:03,718 --> 00:30:06,345
- Look at that one.
- Yeah.

473
00:30:06,429 --> 00:30:07,972
LICENSE FOR
LIVESTOCK ARTIFICIAL INSEMINATION

474
00:30:09,557 --> 00:30:11,392
PATENT, PRODUCT REGISTRATION CERTIFICATE

475
00:30:15,229 --> 00:30:16,647
You can read it one last time

476
00:30:16,731 --> 00:30:18,607
- and sign it if it's okay.
- Okay.

477
00:30:22,611 --> 00:30:24,697
- What are you doing?
- Hey.

478
00:30:25,448 --> 00:30:27,700
He's my son. He helps me with the farm.

479
00:30:27,867 --> 00:30:29,160
They're from the hotel.

480
00:30:31,579 --> 00:30:32,621
Hello.

481
00:30:33,456 --> 00:30:38,377
My father is a very hardworking farmer.
I look forward to working with you.

482
00:30:38,461 --> 00:30:40,212
We'll do our best, too.

483
00:30:40,296 --> 00:30:41,672
Thank you.

484
00:30:46,510 --> 00:30:48,888
HANKUK UNIVERSITY HOSPITAL

485
00:30:53,100 --> 00:30:54,977
You must be tired.

486
00:30:55,811 --> 00:30:58,689
I'm exhausted.

487
00:30:58,773 --> 00:31:00,274
Oh, no.

488
00:31:00,691 --> 00:31:01,984
What should we eat after?

489
00:31:02,068 --> 00:31:04,445
- Maybe chueotang?
- Sounds good.

490
00:31:05,821 --> 00:31:07,031
It was so good last time.

491
00:31:07,114 --> 00:31:08,532
- I know.
- Ms. Park Jeong-im.

492
00:31:08,783 --> 00:31:11,327
- Yes.
- Please head to the MRI room.

493
00:31:11,410 --> 00:31:12,411
Okay.

494
00:31:14,330 --> 00:31:18,292
The two suites are far from each other.
Is that okay?

495
00:31:18,417 --> 00:31:22,171
There are two twin rooms
that are close to each other.

496
00:31:22,838 --> 00:31:26,258
It's okay. Double suites are better.

497
00:31:26,342 --> 00:31:28,886
Of course, we can text each other
if we need.

498
00:31:28,969 --> 00:31:30,304
The bigger the bed, the better.

499
00:31:30,846 --> 00:31:32,723
- Yeah.
- Okay, I'll give you the keys.

500
00:31:34,809 --> 00:31:36,060
- Here.
- Thank you.

501
00:31:36,143 --> 00:31:37,520
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

502
00:31:40,981 --> 00:31:43,109
What do you want to do for dinner?

503
00:31:43,567 --> 00:31:45,111
If you're okay...

504
00:31:45,403 --> 00:31:50,116
Don't mind me at all.
You can enjoy your alone time.

505
00:31:51,492 --> 00:31:52,576
Sure, then.

506
00:32:08,092 --> 00:32:09,427
Tae-seop!

507
00:32:09,677 --> 00:32:10,678
Hey, Ui-yeong.

508
00:32:13,472 --> 00:32:15,766
- Let's go to the beach first.
- Sounds good!

509
00:32:23,399 --> 00:32:26,110
- In the pool? I'll get you a floatie.
- Yeah.

510
00:32:30,239 --> 00:32:31,323
It's stunning.

511
00:32:56,223 --> 00:32:58,142
It looks like a snow-covered mountain.

512
00:32:58,225 --> 00:32:59,768
Yeah, it looks like a mountain.

513
00:32:59,977 --> 00:33:01,061
With snow on top.

514
00:33:01,270 --> 00:33:02,271
I hear something!

515
00:33:03,272 --> 00:33:04,273
Check it out!

516
00:33:08,903 --> 00:33:09,904
Ui-yeong!

517
00:33:42,228 --> 00:33:44,021
This is just the best.

518
00:33:44,104 --> 00:33:46,649
Does the beach look the same as it did
when you were a kid?

519
00:33:50,110 --> 00:33:51,612
I don't think anything's changed.

520
00:33:52,905 --> 00:33:54,532
I guess the ocean doesn't age.

521
00:33:55,533 --> 00:33:56,534
I guess not.

522
00:33:57,159 --> 00:34:00,496
Maybe that's why I feel so calm
when I look at the ocean.

523
00:34:02,581 --> 00:34:05,209
Your feet are covered in sand now.

524
00:34:05,292 --> 00:34:07,336
It's fine. I can dust it off.

525
00:34:10,130 --> 00:34:11,799
This is what I love about you.

526
00:34:11,882 --> 00:34:13,175
Hmm? What?

527
00:34:14,552 --> 00:34:16,720
When you take a dog on a walk

528
00:34:17,137 --> 00:34:19,890
you see them running
to their favorite things

529
00:34:20,015 --> 00:34:22,726
regardless of their feet
getting wet or dirty.

530
00:34:23,352 --> 00:34:25,437
That's the loveliest thing about them.

531
00:34:26,605 --> 00:34:29,024
Aud you're the same.

532
00:34:31,110 --> 00:34:33,737
And I love this about you.

533
00:34:34,071 --> 00:34:35,114
Hmm?

534
00:34:36,031 --> 00:34:39,994
You find every little thing about me
so cute and lovable.

535
00:34:41,370 --> 00:34:46,000
That makes me want to show you
more of myself.

536
00:34:48,586 --> 00:34:49,587
I love that.

537
00:35:05,060 --> 00:35:08,647
The farmer recommended
a sashimi restaurant. You want to go?

538
00:35:08,814 --> 00:35:09,898
Sounds good.

539
00:35:10,357 --> 00:35:13,235
Is Hyun-min not having dinner?

540
00:35:13,527 --> 00:35:15,613
Maybe she's sleeping.
She hasn't checked my texts.

541
00:35:15,738 --> 00:35:16,739
What?

542
00:35:18,657 --> 00:35:19,825
Here.

543
00:35:20,492 --> 00:35:21,577
That was fun.

544
00:35:25,539 --> 00:35:29,084
YEONGGEUM SEAFOOD

545
00:35:39,970 --> 00:35:42,306
Sorry! We're closed for the day.

546
00:35:42,389 --> 00:35:45,184
-Sorry?
- We have a 100-group limit. Try tomorrow.

547
00:35:45,267 --> 00:35:47,603
Oh, no, we came from far away, though.

548
00:35:47,686 --> 00:35:48,979
We're heading back tomorrow.

549
00:35:49,688 --> 00:35:51,023
Sorry about that.

550
00:35:54,568 --> 00:35:55,944
This is so sad.

551
00:35:56,028 --> 00:35:59,323
Should we look for another spot?
I saw a lot of seafood restaurants around.

552
00:35:59,406 --> 00:36:01,408
We have no choice. Let's go.

553
00:36:05,954 --> 00:36:06,955
Oh?

554
00:36:07,498 --> 00:36:09,124
- Why?
- Tae-seop

555
00:36:10,209 --> 00:36:11,669
it looks like we can eat here.

556
00:36:14,046 --> 00:36:15,047
Oh!

557
00:36:20,177 --> 00:36:22,846
- Ah!
- Ah!

558
00:36:24,264 --> 00:36:25,683
- Ui-yeong!
- Look at that.

559
00:36:25,766 --> 00:36:28,894
I thought you were sleeping,
but you were sneaking your guy along!

560
00:36:30,729 --> 00:36:34,108
I don't think I'm the only one
killing two birds with one stone here.

561
00:36:34,358 --> 00:36:37,277
That explains what you said
when we were checking in...

562
00:36:37,361 --> 00:36:38,862
The bed...

563
00:36:41,156 --> 00:36:42,157
Wait!

564
00:36:42,491 --> 00:36:45,786
So, my Min is colleagues with Ui-yeong?

565
00:36:45,869 --> 00:36:48,664
Yeah, Jun, how do you know Ui-yeong?

566
00:36:49,331 --> 00:36:51,834
"Min" and "Jun"? My gosh.

567
00:36:53,585 --> 00:36:56,088
I helped you two save your relationship.

568
00:36:58,132 --> 00:37:00,008
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

569
00:37:05,264 --> 00:37:08,058
- So, you were Choco Killer.
- Yeah.

570
00:37:09,768 --> 00:37:12,229
Let me make you a ssam to thank you.

571
00:37:12,521 --> 00:37:15,733
No need for that.
Please just get along. Don't fight.

572
00:37:15,816 --> 00:37:18,569
Even if you fight, don't call me, okay?

573
00:37:19,069 --> 00:37:20,612
We'll make sure that doesn't happen.

574
00:37:21,530 --> 00:37:23,031
- Ah!
- Ah.

575
00:37:23,407 --> 00:37:24,491
What a cutie!

576
00:37:25,576 --> 00:37:28,454
So, you knew each other for years, right?

577
00:37:28,537 --> 00:37:30,289
How was my Jun in college?

578
00:37:30,372 --> 00:37:33,250
Was he super popular?
Did he have fan girls following him?

579
00:37:35,294 --> 00:37:38,422
I know he looks like a human now

580
00:37:38,505 --> 00:37:42,634
but you wouldn't have wanted to date him
if you'd met him college, either.

581
00:37:45,095 --> 00:37:46,430
Excuse me.

582
00:37:46,638 --> 00:37:49,016
- You were a total loser, too!
- Hey!

583
00:37:50,142 --> 00:37:53,270
But Ui-yeong was so smart in school.

584
00:37:53,353 --> 00:37:56,315
She knew how to find seats at the library,
get cheap coffee

585
00:37:56,565 --> 00:37:59,067
and even sign up for a savings account
for a house.

586
00:37:59,151 --> 00:38:02,112
We were basically friends for survival.

587
00:38:02,196 --> 00:38:03,197
That's right.

588
00:38:03,489 --> 00:38:06,533
I knew Ui-yeong was always smart!

589
00:38:07,159 --> 00:38:11,955
My Jun! You were such a good friend!
What a cutie.

590
00:38:12,206 --> 00:38:14,124
You're a cutie, too, my Min.

591
00:38:15,292 --> 00:38:17,044
Here's your favorite, Min.

592
00:38:17,503 --> 00:38:20,506
- Say ah!
- Ah!

593
00:38:20,589 --> 00:38:22,674
YEONGGEUM SEAFOOD

594
00:38:22,758 --> 00:38:26,261
How about an afterparty at a karaoke bar?

595
00:38:27,095 --> 00:38:29,264
- That hurts.
- We should head back to the hotel.

596
00:38:29,348 --> 00:38:30,390
You want to do that?

597
00:38:30,974 --> 00:38:33,352
We'll just take a walk before we go.

598
00:38:33,435 --> 00:38:35,145
I want to take you somewhere.

599
00:38:35,437 --> 00:38:36,605
Where? Ouch!

600
00:38:37,397 --> 00:38:38,857
You're going to rip my side out!

601
00:38:38,941 --> 00:38:40,108
Okay, see you in Seoul.

602
00:38:40,192 --> 00:38:41,276
Okay, see you.

603
00:38:41,777 --> 00:38:43,320
- I'll text you. Bye.
- Bye.

604
00:38:43,445 --> 00:38:45,322
- Bye.
- Have a good night!

605
00:38:45,405 --> 00:38:46,406
You too!

606
00:38:48,826 --> 00:38:50,327
They look so good together.

607
00:38:51,078 --> 00:38:52,913
- Bye!
- Goodnight!

608
00:38:56,667 --> 00:39:00,420
- Bye! Drive safely!
- Bye!

609
00:39:04,091 --> 00:39:08,220
Shouldn't they be
in their honeymoon phase?

610
00:39:08,428 --> 00:39:09,721
But I feel like they'd go

611
00:39:10,097 --> 00:39:15,727
"Tilt your head to the right,
and I'll go the other way"

612
00:39:15,853 --> 00:39:18,146
when they kiss, right?

613
00:39:18,856 --> 00:39:21,066
Why? I think they look cute together.

614
00:39:21,608 --> 00:39:25,529
I haven't seen Ui-yeong so relaxed
around someone in forever.

615
00:39:26,530 --> 00:39:29,241
- And you know what Tae-seop said?
- Hmm?

616
00:39:29,366 --> 00:39:30,742
- I'm ready to pay.
- Okay.

617
00:39:30,826 --> 00:39:32,411
- We'll pay with this card.
- Okay.

618
00:39:36,290 --> 00:39:39,459
This is my first trip with Ui-yeong.

619
00:39:39,793 --> 00:39:42,129
I want to spend some time alone with her

620
00:39:42,296 --> 00:39:45,299
- so is it okay if we go on our own later?
- Sure.

621
00:39:46,091 --> 00:39:49,011
My heart skipped a beat, and I'm a man.

622
00:39:49,720 --> 00:39:51,638
That's a real man.

623
00:39:52,764 --> 00:39:55,100
- You think so?
- Yeah.

624
00:39:56,768 --> 00:39:57,811
Ready to go?

625
00:39:58,186 --> 00:40:00,188
- Shall we?
- Let's go!

626
00:40:04,818 --> 00:40:06,153
That's stunning.

627
00:40:06,236 --> 00:40:07,988
Is this where you wanted to come?

628
00:40:08,071 --> 00:40:09,114
I want to ride it!

629
00:40:10,490 --> 00:40:13,577
I knew it was a view spot,
but it's so tall.

630
00:40:14,536 --> 00:40:16,580
We don't need to get on it. We can just...

631
00:40:17,497 --> 00:40:18,498
look at it.

632
00:40:20,000 --> 00:40:23,921
You can see
the ocean and the city at once!

633
00:40:24,004 --> 00:40:25,213
That's so cool.

634
00:40:25,589 --> 00:40:27,841
Oh, you can see everything...

635
00:40:28,800 --> 00:40:33,013
It would've been awesome
if there were fireworks by the beach.

636
00:40:33,096 --> 00:40:36,183
There's always fireworks
at the beach, you know?

637
00:40:36,266 --> 00:40:38,018
Oh, right. Yeah.

638
00:40:42,105 --> 00:40:44,650
You've been a bit off since earlier.

639
00:40:44,733 --> 00:40:45,734
What do you mean?

640
00:40:46,234 --> 00:40:48,111
Are you scared?

641
00:40:49,112 --> 00:40:51,323
No, I'm not scared at all.

642
00:40:52,449 --> 00:40:53,992
Yeah, you are!

643
00:41:00,582 --> 00:41:01,917
- Here.
- Hmm?

644
00:41:03,794 --> 00:41:04,962
I'll hold your hands.

645
00:41:05,045 --> 00:41:06,296
Not scary anymore, right?

646
00:41:07,547 --> 00:41:08,590
I don't know...

647
00:41:08,674 --> 00:41:10,008
I guess it's not helping.

648
00:41:14,763 --> 00:41:17,057
Here. Just look at me.

649
00:41:18,850 --> 00:41:19,977
Not scary anymore, right?

650
00:41:25,148 --> 00:41:26,441
Not at all.

651
00:41:32,781 --> 00:41:34,700
- Look far away.
- Far away? Where?

652
00:41:34,783 --> 00:41:37,911
Over there. Not up. Look at the view.

653
00:41:46,169 --> 00:41:49,673
I didn't know
you'd booked a room for yourself.

654
00:41:51,842 --> 00:41:54,928
I thought you might be sharing a room
with Hyun-min.

655
00:41:58,432 --> 00:42:00,017
I guess I get it.

656
00:42:05,022 --> 00:42:06,273
It's so slow.

657
00:42:07,899 --> 00:42:08,942
Yeah.

658
00:42:12,154 --> 00:42:13,405
The door is opening.

659
00:42:14,781 --> 00:42:16,450
Goodnight. I'll call you later.

660
00:42:17,701 --> 00:42:18,702
Wait.

661
00:42:22,122 --> 00:42:24,082
Sure, I booked another room

662
00:42:24,291 --> 00:42:26,043
but I didn't say we'd sleep separately.

663
00:42:26,334 --> 00:42:27,377
What?

664
00:42:30,005 --> 00:42:31,048
Let's...

665
00:42:32,299 --> 00:42:33,592
stay together tonight.

666
00:43:41,785 --> 00:43:43,411
- Are you up?
- Yeah.

667
00:43:44,704 --> 00:43:46,748
We should get ready to leave now.

668
00:43:46,832 --> 00:43:48,750
No! I don't want to.

669
00:43:51,044 --> 00:43:52,379
Let's stay here for a bit more.

670
00:43:55,882 --> 00:43:56,883
Just a bit more.

671
00:43:59,594 --> 00:44:01,638
This is so nice.

672
00:44:04,307 --> 00:44:05,934
I really don't want to leave.

673
00:44:06,017 --> 00:44:08,979
- But we have to go.
- Okay, in just a bit!

674
00:44:36,464 --> 00:44:39,009
I'm heading down now.
I'll see you at the reception.

675
00:44:41,720 --> 00:44:42,721
Oh?

676
00:44:44,931 --> 00:44:46,183
Oh, gosh.

677
00:44:47,475 --> 00:44:49,019
- Are you okay?
- Yeah.

678
00:44:50,228 --> 00:44:51,229
Huh?

679
00:44:51,313 --> 00:44:53,940
- Oh, it's all torn.
- Just a sec.

680
00:44:55,692 --> 00:44:57,569
Could I get a paper bag, please?

681
00:45:02,741 --> 00:45:03,742
Here you go, sir.

682
00:45:04,242 --> 00:45:05,785
Thank you.

683
00:45:05,869 --> 00:45:06,870
You're welcome.

684
00:45:08,413 --> 00:45:09,456
Hey, Ui-yeong.

685
00:45:12,751 --> 00:45:13,960
- Dad!
- Oh?

686
00:45:14,794 --> 00:45:16,880
Ui-yeong! What are you doing here?

687
00:45:17,547 --> 00:45:18,548
What?

688
00:45:18,798 --> 00:45:21,134
Your father?

689
00:45:21,676 --> 00:45:22,677
Yeah.

690
00:45:25,305 --> 00:45:26,306
Huh?

691
00:45:29,768 --> 00:45:31,645
LEE TAE-SUNG

692
00:45:32,020 --> 00:45:34,231
What brings you here?

693
00:45:34,314 --> 00:45:35,857
I thought you were in Gyeongju.

694
00:45:35,941 --> 00:45:39,110
Yeah, but there's a new line
being built to Sokcho.

695
00:45:39,194 --> 00:45:40,570
And I'm here for a workshop.

696
00:45:41,655 --> 00:45:44,449
So, are you two on a trip?

697
00:45:45,158 --> 00:45:46,326
No.

698
00:45:46,451 --> 00:45:49,663
I had to come here for work,
so he just tagged along.

699
00:45:50,789 --> 00:45:52,374
Who knew this would happen?

700
00:45:52,582 --> 00:45:54,542
I can't believe
I'm meeting your boyfriend.

701
00:45:55,627 --> 00:45:58,296
Well, I didn't bring him here to meet you.
It was a coincidence.

702
00:45:58,421 --> 00:45:59,589
Right.

703
00:45:59,839 --> 00:46:01,466
That's even more surprising.

704
00:46:01,716 --> 00:46:03,551
Maybe this is meant to be!

705
00:46:06,972 --> 00:46:12,018
Do you like Tae-seop
because he looks like me?

706
00:46:12,560 --> 00:46:13,687
- What?
- Just look!

707
00:46:13,770 --> 00:46:16,273
Tae-seop and Tae-sung.
Our names sound similar.

708
00:46:16,356 --> 00:46:17,691
We look alike, too.

709
00:46:17,774 --> 00:46:21,111
He has a small face with clear skin
and long limbs.

710
00:46:21,361 --> 00:46:23,655
He also has kind eyes, and...

711
00:46:23,738 --> 00:46:27,117
You really haven't changed a bit.

712
00:46:29,077 --> 00:46:30,453
Of course.

713
00:46:31,329 --> 00:46:34,249
Like the fact that you're my daughter,
no matter how old you become.

714
00:46:38,169 --> 00:46:40,422
I've been thinking a lot
about the old days lately.

715
00:46:40,880 --> 00:46:42,632
I missed a lot of important moments

716
00:46:42,882 --> 00:46:46,219
over trivial things in my life.

717
00:46:47,721 --> 00:46:50,724
I should've done everything
to stay with you and your mom.

718
00:46:54,769 --> 00:46:55,812
Hold on.

719
00:46:59,941 --> 00:47:02,110
- I'd better get going.
- Okay.

720
00:47:05,697 --> 00:47:07,699
- Take this.
- No, it's fine.

721
00:47:07,782 --> 00:47:10,452
- No, you sent me fruit, too. Here.
- No.

722
00:47:10,535 --> 00:47:11,786
It's fine.

723
00:47:13,330 --> 00:47:15,874
Use this to pay for gas

724
00:47:15,957 --> 00:47:17,917
and get Ui-yeong some chocolate,
her favorite.

725
00:47:20,503 --> 00:47:21,629
Let's meet more often.

726
00:47:22,339 --> 00:47:24,507
I'll really do my best.

727
00:47:27,093 --> 00:47:28,428
- Bye.
- Yeah.

728
00:47:29,304 --> 00:47:30,347
Goodbye, sir.

729
00:47:49,407 --> 00:47:50,492
Are you okay?

730
00:47:53,703 --> 00:47:54,829
It's so fascinating

731
00:47:55,830 --> 00:47:57,374
how uncomfortable I am

732
00:47:57,457 --> 00:48:01,252
yet my dad acts
like we've been close this whole time.

733
00:48:03,213 --> 00:48:06,966
He seems very cheerful and kind.

734
00:48:08,218 --> 00:48:09,594
He's always been like that.

735
00:48:10,845 --> 00:48:14,265
But maybe you only saw the best of him

736
00:48:14,682 --> 00:48:18,103
because we met him on his good day.

737
00:48:18,436 --> 00:48:19,479
I see.

738
00:48:20,271 --> 00:48:22,399
What's your mother like?

739
00:48:22,482 --> 00:48:23,942
- My mom?
- Yeah.

740
00:48:24,234 --> 00:48:25,735
She has quite the temper.

741
00:48:28,154 --> 00:48:31,241
She's rational,
always standing up for what's right

742
00:48:31,408 --> 00:48:33,159
and she's no easier on her family.

743
00:48:34,869 --> 00:48:37,497
They're really different.

744
00:48:37,997 --> 00:48:40,125
I see why it must've been hard
to live together.

745
00:48:41,751 --> 00:48:44,337
And I respect their decision.

746
00:48:48,049 --> 00:48:50,093
That was a really great trip,
all thanks to you.

747
00:48:50,635 --> 00:48:51,678
Same.

748
00:48:53,513 --> 00:48:55,723
I've traveled a lot for work

749
00:48:55,807 --> 00:49:00,603
but this is my first real vacation
in five or six years.

750
00:49:00,687 --> 00:49:03,064
I usually just do nothing at home.

751
00:49:03,148 --> 00:49:05,525
I'm not the type to travel around
by myself.

752
00:49:05,608 --> 00:49:06,609
I see.

753
00:49:07,819 --> 00:49:09,154
Five to six years ago?

754
00:49:13,491 --> 00:49:16,077
Who did you travel with then?

755
00:49:17,036 --> 00:49:20,457
Should we book the same days off
for the next vacation?

756
00:49:20,540 --> 00:49:21,958
Yeah, so who did you travel with?

757
00:49:22,041 --> 00:49:23,376
- Next month?
- Tell me.

758
00:49:23,460 --> 00:49:25,420
Tell me
who you went on your last trip with!

759
00:49:25,503 --> 00:49:26,880
Or maybe the month after?

760
00:49:28,882 --> 00:49:30,925
I'll let you off the hook today.

761
00:49:31,050 --> 00:49:32,135
Thanks.

762
00:50:03,666 --> 00:50:05,293
Are you going back to work tomorrow?

763
00:50:05,960 --> 00:50:07,754
Yeah, I am.

764
00:50:08,254 --> 00:50:12,133
But I'm extra sad to say goodbye
after spending so much time together.

765
00:50:13,676 --> 00:50:14,844
Hug me before you go, then.

766
00:50:19,599 --> 00:50:21,809
- That was so much fun.
- I don't want to go.

767
00:50:21,893 --> 00:50:23,937
- Let's go again soon.
- Okay.

768
00:50:28,525 --> 00:50:30,193
- Drive safely.
- Okay.

769
00:50:31,444 --> 00:50:32,529
Ui-yeong?

770
00:50:32,946 --> 00:50:34,030
Mom!

771
00:50:34,280 --> 00:50:35,281
"Mom"?

772
00:50:35,907 --> 00:50:38,409
You're kidding me.
First, Dad, and now, Mom?

773
00:50:38,701 --> 00:50:40,161
What's in the air today?

774
00:50:41,162 --> 00:50:42,330
Who are you?

775
00:50:45,333 --> 00:50:46,751
Mom, he's...

776
00:50:47,001 --> 00:50:49,420
He's my boyfriend.

777
00:50:50,505 --> 00:50:51,756
She's my mom.

778
00:50:51,881 --> 00:50:53,341
- Hello.
- Hello.

779
00:50:53,424 --> 00:50:54,676
He was just about to leave!

780
00:50:54,759 --> 00:50:56,427
- You should get going.
- What? But...

781
00:50:56,678 --> 00:50:58,888
- I can't just leave...
- You're busy! Go!

782
00:50:58,972 --> 00:51:00,515
- Hey...
- Go!

783
00:51:01,891 --> 00:51:02,976
Let's head in.

784
00:51:03,059 --> 00:51:04,602
- I'm exhausted.
- Goodbye.

785
00:51:04,686 --> 00:51:06,437
- Bye!
- Okay, bye.

786
00:51:06,521 --> 00:51:07,522
- Go!
- See you around.

787
00:51:07,605 --> 00:51:08,856
- Okay.
- Bye.

788
00:51:11,025 --> 00:51:12,026
Oh, gosh.

789
00:51:17,282 --> 00:51:18,741
I need to rest.

790
00:51:18,825 --> 00:51:20,243
So

791
00:51:21,119 --> 00:51:22,704
you've been seeing someone, huh?

792
00:51:24,372 --> 00:51:27,792
I met him on a blind date
and started dating him.

793
00:51:28,001 --> 00:51:29,127
It was pretty recent.

794
00:51:29,252 --> 00:51:32,589
I was going to tell you,
but you seemed busy.

795
00:51:32,672 --> 00:51:34,507
I didn't know if you were even curious.

796
00:51:34,591 --> 00:51:36,092
Why wouldn't I be curious?

797
00:51:36,217 --> 00:51:38,761
You chose him
after millions of blind dates.

798
00:51:39,846 --> 00:51:42,515
Don't tell me he's the carpoor guy.

799
00:51:43,766 --> 00:51:46,019
- Huh?
- Is he?

800
00:51:47,061 --> 00:51:51,107
Why couldn't you have found yourself
a proper guy?

801
00:51:51,190 --> 00:51:53,651
That was all a misunderstanding.

802
00:51:53,985 --> 00:51:55,862
Tae-seop isn't carpoor

803
00:51:56,321 --> 00:51:58,031
and he's really great.

804
00:51:59,616 --> 00:52:00,658
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

805
00:52:01,284 --> 00:52:03,953
Bring him home one day, then.
Let me meet him.

806
00:52:04,037 --> 00:52:05,496
Hmm? Why?

807
00:52:05,580 --> 00:52:07,957
I want to know why he even likes you

808
00:52:08,041 --> 00:52:10,877
and you know I have a good eye for people.

809
00:52:10,960 --> 00:52:11,961
You?

810
00:52:15,423 --> 00:52:17,634
You really want to meet him?

811
00:52:17,717 --> 00:52:21,179
Yeah, set a date and tell me. I'm serious.

812
00:52:22,472 --> 00:52:24,515
Okay, then.

813
00:52:25,391 --> 00:52:27,435
- I'm getting groceries.
- Okay.

814
00:52:34,192 --> 00:52:36,819
So, she wants me to bring you home.

815
00:52:37,362 --> 00:52:38,780
It's too much, right?

816
00:52:38,905 --> 00:52:41,115
No, I'm fine with that.

817
00:52:41,199 --> 00:52:44,494
I was so surprised earlier
that I couldn't introduce myself properly.

818
00:52:44,869 --> 00:52:48,956
And I'm sure it doesn't sit right with you
that I've only met your dad.

819
00:52:50,458 --> 00:52:52,752
Yeah, that's true.

820
00:52:53,294 --> 00:52:55,797
How about next Saturday, then?

821
00:52:55,880 --> 00:52:57,215
Sure, that sounds good.

822
00:52:57,298 --> 00:52:59,092
What does she like?

823
00:52:59,175 --> 00:53:00,635
My mom?

824
00:53:01,636 --> 00:53:02,804
Well...

825
00:53:03,221 --> 00:53:06,516
Her favorite thing is alcohol.

826
00:53:08,059 --> 00:53:09,060
Alcohol...

827
00:53:09,811 --> 00:53:12,855
So, why don't you buy
her second-favorite thing, flowers?

828
00:53:14,023 --> 00:53:16,526
Oh, yeah, I'll do that.

829
00:53:17,485 --> 00:53:19,320
- Thank you.
- Okay.

830
00:53:23,074 --> 00:53:24,117
Alcohol...

831
00:53:38,756 --> 00:53:44,971
SONG TAE-SEOP

832
00:53:46,556 --> 00:53:49,308
By the way, can you check inside your bag?

833
00:53:58,860 --> 00:54:02,655
I'm glad to have shared the time with you.
Let's love like the ocean.

834
00:54:12,165 --> 00:54:15,752
DINNER WITH MOM AND TAE-SEOP

835
00:54:18,546 --> 00:54:20,590
DINNER WITH MOM AND TAE-SEOP

836
00:54:25,344 --> 00:54:27,013
Welcome back, Ui-yeong.

837
00:54:27,096 --> 00:54:28,723
- Na-ri!
- Did you have a good break?

838
00:54:28,806 --> 00:54:31,100
Yeah, all thanks to your understanding.

839
00:54:32,059 --> 00:54:35,104
The gift set is all ready now

840
00:54:35,188 --> 00:54:37,940
and you can get updates on everything else
at the meeting.

841
00:54:38,024 --> 00:54:39,025
Okay.

842
00:54:40,026 --> 00:54:44,280
And you know I'm the team leader
while Mr. Oh is on probation, right?

843
00:54:45,281 --> 00:54:47,950
You can just call me Ms. Jung.

844
00:54:48,576 --> 00:54:50,453
- Let's work hard.
- Okay.

845
00:54:52,038 --> 00:54:53,372
Ms. Jung...

846
00:54:54,415 --> 00:54:56,918
Hey, Na-ri!
Are those prescription glasses?

847
00:54:57,210 --> 00:54:58,544
Of course, they are.

848
00:54:58,711 --> 00:54:59,837
Let's work hard, okay?

849
00:55:07,804 --> 00:55:11,474
She seems to be really enjoying her time
as a temporary team leader.

850
00:55:16,395 --> 00:55:19,357
Hmm? Is something bothering you?

851
00:55:19,857 --> 00:55:21,234
Why the long face?

852
00:55:22,235 --> 00:55:27,073
My mom accidentally saw me with Tae-seop.

853
00:55:27,740 --> 00:55:29,826
Now, she wants me to invite him
to our house.

854
00:55:30,952 --> 00:55:34,121
Don't all parents do that?
Maybe she really likes him.

855
00:55:34,413 --> 00:55:37,291
Yeah, all parents do that, but not my mom.

856
00:55:38,000 --> 00:55:39,293
It's so odd.

857
00:55:42,964 --> 00:55:44,006
What's going on?

858
00:55:52,348 --> 00:55:53,891
Ms. Park Jeong-im.

859
00:55:53,975 --> 00:55:55,059
Oh, here.

860
00:56:00,273 --> 00:56:02,191
I got a health check-up done

861
00:56:02,650 --> 00:56:06,529
and the MRA showed
signs of a cerebral aneurysm.

862
00:56:08,948 --> 00:56:11,784
Do you get headaches or dizzy often?

863
00:56:11,868 --> 00:56:15,997
No, nothing noticeable.

864
00:56:16,080 --> 00:56:17,623
I also have no family history of it.

865
00:56:17,707 --> 00:56:20,126
It's more common for them
to be asymptomatic.

866
00:56:20,209 --> 00:56:22,753
Some discover them
through check-ups, like you

867
00:56:22,837 --> 00:56:25,590
and others discover them
when they rupture and cause a hemorrhage.

868
00:56:25,715 --> 00:56:26,757
Cerebral hemorrhage?

869
00:56:27,216 --> 00:56:28,384
Just in the worst case.

870
00:56:28,467 --> 00:56:30,887
Its risk depends
on the size and the location

871
00:56:30,970 --> 00:56:32,513
so let's do a detailed check-up.

872
00:56:32,889 --> 00:56:35,057
Try to sleep well for the next few days

873
00:56:35,433 --> 00:56:38,561
and stay away from alcohol, smoking,
and stressful environments.

874
00:56:38,644 --> 00:56:39,645
Okay.

875
00:56:46,444 --> 00:56:48,696
Jeong-im?

876
00:56:50,406 --> 00:56:52,033
- Jeong-im!
- Yeah.

877
00:56:52,408 --> 00:56:54,702
Did you go to the doctor? What did he say?

878
00:56:54,785 --> 00:56:57,496
He wants me to get some further testing.

879
00:56:58,623 --> 00:56:59,624
Oh, gosh.

880
00:57:01,292 --> 00:57:02,752
Have you told your daughter yet?

881
00:57:03,252 --> 00:57:04,253
Not yet.

882
00:57:04,754 --> 00:57:07,381
I'll tell her once I'm sure of it
after the check-up.

883
00:57:08,007 --> 00:57:11,260
And I'm seeing her boyfriend this weekend.

884
00:57:11,469 --> 00:57:13,012
Is she seeing someone?

885
00:57:13,095 --> 00:57:14,764
After all those blind dates!

886
00:57:14,847 --> 00:57:17,266
I caught the two hugging.

887
00:57:19,769 --> 00:57:20,811
You know

888
00:57:21,145 --> 00:57:24,315
I just invited him for a meal
to see if he was a good guy.

889
00:57:25,191 --> 00:57:28,694
You need to tell her soon.
She'll be so shocked to hear it later.

890
00:57:28,861 --> 00:57:30,404
You're covered by insurance.

891
00:57:30,571 --> 00:57:34,325
It's not about the money.
I just don't want to worry her.

892
00:57:34,533 --> 00:57:36,369
If I weren't alone

893
00:57:36,452 --> 00:57:39,372
she wouldn't have had to bear
the worry alone.

894
00:57:40,539 --> 00:57:42,291
Are you not going to tell your husband?

895
00:57:44,293 --> 00:57:45,836
What? My husband?

896
00:57:47,004 --> 00:57:50,341
We've lived apart for 20 years.
I'd rather fight whatever this is alone.

897
00:57:50,675 --> 00:57:53,010
There's no way I'm asking him for help.

898
00:57:54,553 --> 00:57:56,722
Yeah, that makes more sense.

899
00:58:13,823 --> 00:58:18,244
Is this a sauna or what?
Everyone's sighing

900
00:58:18,327 --> 00:58:21,205
and the air feels so gloomy.

901
00:58:21,288 --> 00:58:24,750
I'm meeting Ui-yeong's mother
this weekend.

902
00:58:24,834 --> 00:58:28,129
You guys are that serious already?
That's so fast!

903
00:58:28,462 --> 00:58:33,718
You want my secret that stole
my mother-in-law's heart?

904
00:58:34,218 --> 00:58:35,219
What?

905
00:58:35,761 --> 00:58:39,223
It's like a blind date, but different.

906
00:58:39,306 --> 00:58:41,017
It's not about impressing her.

907
00:58:41,100 --> 00:58:43,894
It's about the actions you make
to show that you're trying.

908
00:58:44,061 --> 00:58:45,521
- Actions...
- Mother-in-laws love

909
00:58:45,604 --> 00:58:47,648
seeing their son-in-laws
trying to impress them.

910
00:58:48,524 --> 00:58:51,569
I got flowers, her favorite,
and planned my outfit.

911
00:58:51,652 --> 00:58:52,737
Okay, here's what you do.

912
00:58:53,195 --> 00:58:56,365
"I prepared flowers
because I heard you love them

913
00:58:56,657 --> 00:58:59,118
and tried to dress up for the occasion.
Is this okay?"

914
00:58:59,201 --> 00:59:00,703
That's what you say, okay?

915
00:59:00,953 --> 00:59:02,913
Shouldn't I sound more confident?

916
00:59:02,997 --> 00:59:05,166
No, listen. "I prepared flowers for you

917
00:59:05,249 --> 00:59:07,084
and dressed up today. Do I look okay?"

918
00:59:07,168 --> 00:59:08,669
That doesn't sound human enough.

919
00:59:08,753 --> 00:59:11,338
You have to make it really clear
that you're making an effort.

920
00:59:11,422 --> 00:59:13,257
- You really don't get it. Next.
- Got it.

921
00:59:13,466 --> 00:59:15,885
Oh, my liver isn't ready.

922
00:59:15,968 --> 00:59:17,386
Apparently, she loves to drink.

923
00:59:18,095 --> 00:59:21,223
You should take
at least two hangover pills before you go.

924
00:59:21,557 --> 00:59:22,767
- Two?
- Yeah.

925
00:59:22,933 --> 00:59:25,227
Even if you get tipsy,
try not to act like it.

926
00:59:25,311 --> 00:59:27,813
And show enthusiastic reactions
whenever she talks.

927
00:59:27,897 --> 00:59:31,650
Answer her loud and clear.
Don't get too shy.

928
00:59:32,651 --> 00:59:34,236
- Loud and clear.
- Blink your eyes

929
00:59:34,403 --> 00:59:35,738
and go, "Yes!"

930
00:59:35,821 --> 00:59:37,823
- I'm not sure about that.
- Yeah, that was bad.

931
00:59:40,493 --> 00:59:41,619
Alright.

932
00:59:51,754 --> 00:59:53,547
My gosh.

933
00:59:54,090 --> 00:59:55,758
Can you do that more regularly?

934
00:59:56,675 --> 00:59:59,553
It's like you're trying
to rip the floor up.

935
01:00:00,596 --> 01:00:01,972
Come on.

936
01:00:03,390 --> 01:00:04,725
Goodness.

937
01:00:15,986 --> 01:00:19,281
Why are you putting everything away?
We use them!

938
01:00:19,615 --> 01:00:22,660
It needs to be a bit messy
to feel like a home.

939
01:00:22,743 --> 01:00:24,870
But we don't need to show that today.

940
01:00:25,162 --> 01:00:27,081
- Huh?
- And Mom

941
01:00:27,164 --> 01:00:29,583
don't ask him uncomfortable questions,
alright?

942
01:00:29,667 --> 01:00:32,294
And try not to sound too cold.

943
01:00:32,378 --> 01:00:34,880
Try to be nice and friendly, okay?

944
01:00:36,423 --> 01:00:37,591
- Happy now?
- Yeah.

945
01:00:38,467 --> 01:00:40,136
Good for someone who never smiles.

946
01:00:41,804 --> 01:00:44,348
Mom! Why is there no rice?

947
01:00:45,182 --> 01:00:48,185
It'd be poor hospitality
if I cooked the lunch myself.

948
01:00:48,269 --> 01:00:50,396
- I know what to eat.
- What?

949
01:00:52,982 --> 01:00:54,233
Oh, I'd better order it now.

950
01:00:54,692 --> 01:00:56,819
- Is he allergic to anything?
- No, he's not.

951
01:00:56,902 --> 01:00:59,113
- I'm getting eobokjaengban, then.
- Okay.

952
01:00:59,530 --> 01:01:02,741
- Where's my phone?
- I told you to put the towel away!

953
01:01:03,075 --> 01:01:04,243
Seriously.

954
01:01:04,326 --> 01:01:05,786
And the water!

955
01:01:07,830 --> 01:01:10,207
Oh! I have to get rid of the drinks.

956
01:01:30,644 --> 01:01:31,812
Oh, right.

957
01:01:48,996 --> 01:01:50,956
Huh? He's early.

958
01:01:51,081 --> 01:01:52,917
Mom! I think Tae-seop's here!

959
01:01:53,083 --> 01:01:54,084
Coming!

960
01:02:01,342 --> 01:02:02,843
Dad?

961
01:02:06,805 --> 01:02:08,015
Hi, Ui-yeong.

962
01:02:16,523 --> 01:02:17,733
Alright.

963
01:02:24,490 --> 01:02:26,283
It's been a minute.

964
01:02:45,636 --> 01:02:46,679
Ui-yeong.

965
01:02:48,639 --> 01:02:49,723
Tae-seop.

966
01:02:50,349 --> 01:02:52,434
Oh, you're here!

967
01:02:53,519 --> 01:02:55,354
- Come in.
- Yes, sir.

968
01:03:00,442 --> 01:03:01,568
- Hello.
- Hello.

969
01:03:01,652 --> 01:03:03,445
We keep running into each other.

970
01:03:03,529 --> 01:03:06,824
It seems like you're meant to be around
for a long time.

971
01:03:38,397 --> 01:03:41,191
THE PRACTICAL GUIDE TO LOVE

972
01:03:47,906 --> 01:03:50,909
A DATE WITH TAE-SEOP

973
01:04:00,711 --> 01:04:04,006
LET'S LOVE LIKE THE OCEAN

974
01:04:08,761 --> 01:04:12,306
LET'S STAY TOGETHER TONIGHT

975
01:04:14,266 --> 01:04:16,393
That wasn't just for you to meet Tae-seop.

976
01:04:16,602 --> 01:04:18,395
It was also for him to get to know you.

977
01:04:19,271 --> 01:04:20,773
I'm really fine.

978
01:04:20,981 --> 01:04:22,524
Today was just not meant to be.

979
01:04:23,067 --> 01:04:24,985
Why don't you stay here for a while?

980
01:04:25,944 --> 01:04:28,739
Ui-yeong! Why is he driving you to work?

981
01:04:29,281 --> 01:04:30,282
Ji-su.

982
01:04:30,449 --> 01:04:32,576
How do you two know each other?

983
01:04:33,035 --> 01:04:35,287
Are you out right now?

984
01:04:35,621 --> 01:04:36,872
What misunderstanding?

985
01:04:38,040 --> 01:04:39,041
Mom!

986
01:04:39,500 --> 01:04:41,168
- Mom!
- She...

987
01:04:42,252 --> 01:04:43,587
fainted in the lobby.

988
01:04:44,296 --> 01:04:45,672
It's all my fault.

989
01:04:50,844 --> 01:04:52,846
Subtitles by: Min-sun Kim
